article.headline: Seton Hall 94, Navy 56
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- Jordan Theodore scored 18 points and Jeremy Hazell added 17 points, including 11 straight during one stretch, leading Seton Hall to a 94-56 victory over Navy on Tuesday night. Hazell scored 11 straight points in second half as the Pirates (9-1) gradually pulled away from the Midshipmen (4-8), who lost their fourth straight game. After leading 30-23 at the half, Seton Hall went on a 20-2 run over a span of 3:17 of the second half to put the game away. Jeff Robinson, a transfer from Memphis, scored nine points and gave the Pirates life off the bench. He became eligible to play for Seton Hall last Saturday. The Pirates hit 12 3-pointers in the second half and outscored the Midshipmen 64-23 after halftime. Jamel Jackson had 11 points and Herb Pope added 10 for Seton Hall. Chris Harris scored 12 points to lead Navy.
